Daniel Akpeyi’s blunder proved catastrophic as Kaizer Chiefs’ title aspirations were dealt a major blow following a 2-1 defeat by at the hands of Maritzburg United at FNB Stadium last night. The defeat means the gap between leaders Chiefs and second-placed Mamelodi Sundowns is seven points. It was Daylon Claasen’s brace that did it for the Team of Choice, while Chiefs netted through a consolation goal via Samir Nurkovic. • Other Premiership results Baroka 0 – 1 Bidvest Wits; Highlands Park 2 – 0 Bloemfontein Celtic; Mamelodi Sundowns 3 – 0 Chippa United; Stellenbosch 1 –0 SuperSport United. -Staff Reporter